{
  "texts": [
    "Then, we introduce a general framework that adapts LLMs as surrogate users to enhance the recommendation mechanism through attribute-oriented tools.",
    "Problem FormulationIn the context of sequential recommendation, as illustrated in Figure 1, given user 𝑢 with a historical interaction sequence H = {𝑖 1, 𝑖 2,..., 𝑖 𝑛-1 }, the goal is to predict the next item of interest 𝑖 𝑛 ∈ I, where I is the complete item pool.",
    "Conventional RSs retrieve a subset I 𝑐 ⊆ I based on the predicted preferences of user 𝑢.",
    "However, this easily results in the desired item 𝑖 𝑛 being absent from I 𝑐.In this work, we position LLMs as the central controller for recommendation, simulating the user exploration w.r.t.",
    "item attributes in a multi-round manner."
  ]
}